700310f.title: Bronx: 195th Street (West) - Reservoir Avenue
700310f.text:
West 195th Street, north side, between Reservoir Ave. and Jerome
Ave., showing Public School No. 86. At the time of this photograph
the school was located on the east side of Reservoir Ave., at the head
of Strong Street from which it was removed to its present (1937) location.
On the school's original aite was constructed Walton High School. A
modern 5-story elementary school, bearing the same number, was constructed
at the N.E. corner of Reservoir Ave. and West 195th Street. The old
school house now constitutes an annex to the main building.
May 8, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
